is%20change%20in%20demand%20in%20a%20written%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOver%20the%20past%20few%20years%2C%20many%20people%20have%20leaped%20and%20found%20a%20new%20job%2C%26quot%3B%20Bunker%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20while%20employers%20are%20still%20hiring%20at%20a%20healthy%20rate%2C%20the%20demand%20for%20new%20hires%20is%20cooling%20down.%20Less%20demand%20for%20new%20hires%20means%20fewer%20people%20quitting%20old%20jobs%20to%20take%20new%20ones.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompanies%20are%20also%20taking%20back%20some%20of%20their%20power%2C%20particularly%20with%20just%20how%20much%20they%20need%20to%20do%20to%20attract%20talent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAt%20the%20height%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjobs-great-resignation-reshuffle-gen-z-millennials-quitting-switching-careers-2021-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EThe%20Great%20Reshuffle%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20we%20saw%20a%20large%20percentage%20of%20professionals%20quitting%20or%20switching%20jobs%20within%20a%20year%20of%20taking%20on%20a%20new%20role%2C%26quot%3B%20Kory%20Kantenga%2C%20senior%20economist%20at%20LinkedIn%2C%20said%20in%20a%20December%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKantenga%20said%20employers%20were%20offering%20higher%20pay%20and%20other%20kinds%20of%20incentives%20to%20attract%20people%20%26quot%3Bat%20a%20time%20where%20there%20were%20many%20more%20job%20openings%20relative%20to%20people%20looking%20for%20work.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20seen%20that%20shift%20with%20hiring%20slowing%20over%20the%20past%2018%20months%20%E2%80%94%20and%20many%20professionals%20have%20stayed%20in%20their%20current%20roles%20longer%2C%20possibly%20waiting%20out%20the%20uncertainty%20of%20the%20economy%2C%26quot%3B%20Kantenga%20said%20in%20the%20statement%20from%20December.%20%26quot%3BHowever%2C%20we%20expect%20to%20see%20professionals%20put%20more%20focus%20on%20the%20job%20market%20in%202024.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20that%20emphasized%20focus%20comes%20at%20a%20time%20when%20hiring%20hasn't%20really%20been%20surging%20%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%94%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethe%20number%20of%20hires%20fell%20slightly%20in%20November.%20Looking%20ahead%2C%20job%20seekers%20may%20have%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feconomic-outlook-recession-forecast-job-hiring-expectations-inflation-soft-landing-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ehard%20time%20finding%20work%20this%20year%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDaniel%20Zhao%2C%20lead%20economist%20at%20Glassdoor%2C%20pointed%20out%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ein%20his%20recent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%2Fdbzhao_jolts-economy-news-activity-7148340352804966402-DfDq%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ecommentary%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20November's%20quit%20rate%20of%202.2%25%20was%20%26quot%3Blower%20than%20its%202019%20peaks.%26quot%3B%20He%20also%20pointed%20to%20the%20recently%20low%20hiring%20rate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20should%20be%20careful%20about%20reading%20too%20much%20into%201%20month%20of%20data%2C%20but%20the%20more%20reliable%20hires%20%26amp%3B%20quits%20data%20point%20to%20a%20job%20market%20that's%20cooling%20to%20something%20more%20like%202017%E2%80%932018%20than%202019%2C%26quot%3B%20Zhao%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFewer%20people%20resigning%20doesn't%20mean%20workers%20want%20to%20still%20work%20the%20same%20position%20with%20the%20same%20routine%20and%20duties.%20Business%20Insider's%20Juliana%20Kaplan%20reported%20on%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffirst-there-was-quiet-quitting-now-its-become-grumpy-staying-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Egrumpy%20staying%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%2C%20or%20people%20unhappy%20that%20they%20have%20to%20stay%20put.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAaron%20Terrazas%2C%20chief%20economist%20at%20Glassdoor%2C%20said%20in%20a%20written%20statement%20that%