e%20couple%20described%20Cecil%20as%20a%20'goofy%20guy'%20who%20is%20usually%20not%20food-motivated%20but%20apparently%20is%20money-motivated.%20The%20couple%20had%20to%20tape%20together%20the%20destroyed%20bills%20and%20locate%20the%20serial%20numbers%20to%20ensure%20the%20banks%20would%20replace%20them.%20However%2C%20%24450%20remains%20unrecovered.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TIMESOFINDIA.COM%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I'm%20a%20millennial%20DINK%20who's%20never%20having%20children.%20We%20know%20the%20consequences%20and%20it's%20not%20a%20selfish%20choice.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223088%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Jess%20Lorimer%20and%20her%20husband%20Owen%20in%20Thailand.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6596e2e46979d73718206643%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222316%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJessica%20Lorimer%20and%20her%20husband%2C%20Owen%2C%20spend%20the%20money%20they%20save%20by%20not%20having%20kids%20on%20traveling%20to%20places%20like%20Thailand.%3Cp%3EJessica%20Lorimer%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EJess%C2%A0Lorimer%20is%20a%2034-year-old%20business%20owner%20living%20in%20England%20with%20her%20husband%20and%20dog.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20couple%20are%20part%20of%20the%C2%A0%26quot%3Bdouble%20income%2C%20no%20kids%26quot%3B%20demographic%20and%20don't%20plan%20on%20having%20children.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ELorimer%20says%20she%20gets%20more%20backlash%20about%20their%20choice%20than%20her%20husband%2C%20who%20got%20a%20vasectomy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%2034-year-old%20Jess%20Lorimer%2C%20who%20lives%20in%20Winchester%2C%20England%2C%20about%20her%20decision%20not%20to%20have%20kids.%20It's%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20always%20known%20that%20I%20didn't%20want%20children.%20I%20didn't%20have%20a%20hideous%20childhood%2C%20but%20I%20saw%20how%20much%20my%20parents%20gave%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20wanted%20to%20focus%20on%20my%20career%2C%20and%20I%20know%20being%20a%20parent%20is%20an%20overwhelming%20responsibility.%20I%20knew%20I%20didn't%20want%20to%20spend%2024%20hours%20a%20day%20worrying%20about%20another%20human%20being.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20met%20my%20husband%2C%20Owen%2C%20in%202021%20when%20I%20was%2030.%20On%20our%20first%20date%2C%20I%20told%20him%20I%20didn't%20want%20children.%20We'd%20been%20together%20for%20about%20five%20months%20when%20we%20talked%20about%20whether%20he%20could%20live%20without%20having%20kids.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe'd%20been%20in%20relationships%20with%20people%20who%20wanted%20children%2C%20but%20he%20also%20recognized%20that%20having%20kids%20would%20mean%20giving%20up%20lots%20of%20things.%20After%20we%20got%20married%2C%20Owen%20had%20a%20vasectomy%20%E2%80%94%20it%20was%20a%20natural%20decision%20for%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20came%20across%20the%20term%20DINK%2C%20which%20stands%20for%20%26quot%3Bdual%20income%2C%20no%20kids%2C%26quot%3B%20on%20Instagram.%20I%20saw%20the%20term%20DINKWAD%20first%2C%20which%20is%20%26quot%3Bdual%20income%2C%20no%20kids%20with%20a%20dog.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20made%20me%20laugh%20because%20we%20have%20the%20most%20spoiled%20dog.%20It%20was%20nice%20to%20know%20that%20we're%20not%20the%20only%20ones%20who%20prioritize%20things%20in%20our%20lives%20besides%20having%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWe%20have%20more%20disposable%20income%20and%20can%20travel%20more%20as%20DINKs%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20us%2C%20there%20are%20huge%20positives%20in%20being%20DINKs.%20One%20of%20the%20biggest%20benefits%20is%20you%20have%20more%20disposable%20income.%20I%20read%20that%20it%20costs%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thetimes.co.uk%2Fmoney-mentor%2Fincome-budgeting%2Ffamily-finance%2Fstarting-family-baby-costs%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eleast%20%C2%A312%2C400%2C%20or%20about%20%2416%2C000%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20year%20to%20raise%20a%20child.%20I%20prefer%20to%20spend%20that%20money%20on%20things%20like%20professional%20development%20and%20travel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20set%20up%20my%20own%20business%2010%20years%20ago%2C%20and%20it%20may%20not%20have%20grown%20as%20quickly%20if%20I'd%20had%20children%20midway%20through.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20disposable%20income%20means%20we%20can%20go%20on%20big%20trips.%20We%20often%20travel%20at%20Christmas%20because%20we%20don't%20have%20the%20obligation%20of%20grandparents%20or%20extended%20family%20wanting%20to%20see%20grandkids.%20We%20went%20to%20Thailand%20last%20year%2C%20and%20this%20year%2C%20we're%20going%20to%20New%20Zealand.%20We%20also%20climbed%20Mount%20Toubkal%20in%20Morocco%20this%20summer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20can%20also%20prioritize%20long-term%20savings%20in%20a%20way%20that%20those%20with%20children%20can't%20necessarily%20do.%20Last%20year%2C%20we%20took%20financial%20lessons%20and%20experimented%20with%20alternative%20investments%20like%20wine%2C%20cryptocurrency%2C%20and%20rental%20portfolios.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20we're%20older%2C%20we%20hope%20to%20live%20in%20a%20nice%20nursing%20home%20we%20will%20have%20saved%20for.%20I%20imagine%20we'll%20pass%20on%20some%20money%20to%20Owen's%20nephew%20and%20our%20godchildren.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20emotional%20time%20and%20investment%20needed%20to%20raise%20children%20is%20also%20huge.%20We%20use%20that%20time%20and%20energy%20to%20work%20on%20our%20relationship%2C%20our%20careers%2C%20and%20recreational%20pursuits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThere's%20a%20lot%20of%20stigma%20that%20comes%20with%20saying%20you%20don't%20want%20children%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20assume%20that%20you%20hate%20kids%2C%20which%20I%20find%20offensive.%20I%20don't%20hate%20children%3B%20I%20just%20don't%20want%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe've%20thought%20a%20lot%20about%20the%20consequences%20of%20having%20and%20not%20having%20children%2C%20but%20people%20still%20tell%20us%20we'll%20change%20our%20minds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20about%20having%20kids%2C%20we%20politely%20say%20it's%20not%20in%20our%20plan%2C%20but%20people%20have%20strong%20opinions.%20They%20say%20things%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BYour%20biological%20clock%20will%20kick%20in%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20I%20find%20very%20reductive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20woman%2C%20the%20negative%20comments%20are%20usually%20directed%20at%20me.%20People%20ask%20questions%20like%3A%20%26quot%3BHow%20does%20your%20husband%20feel%20about%20you%20removing%20his%20ability%20to%20have%20children%3F%26quot%3B%20If%20Owen%20says%20we%20don't%20want%20kids%2C%20people%20say%20things%20like%3A%20%26quot%3BYour%20wife%20will%20change%20her%20mind.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20doesn't%20put%20a%20strain%20on%20our%20relationship.%20I%20just%20smile.%20I've%20found%20there's%20no%20arguing%20with%20what%20people%20believe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20lot%20of%20our%20friends%20have%20children%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOwen%20has%20one%20nephew%2C%20and%20we%20have%20two%20godchildren.%20We're%20prime%20godparent%20candidates%20because%20we%20have%20disposable%20income%2C%20time%2C%20and%20a%20sense%20of%20humor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe're%20the%20fun%20people%20kids%20like%20spending%20time%20with%2C%20and%20we%20buy%20them%20great%20gifts.%20For%20my%20godson's%20first%20birthday%2C%20I%20bought%20him%20a%20mini%20Rolls-Royce.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20exciting%20to%20be%20part%20of%20their%20lives%20and%20see%20them%20experience%20things%20for%20the%20first%20time%20%E2%80%94%20but%20would%20I%20want%20to%20look%20after%20a%20child%2024%2F7%3F%20Absolutely%20not.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20society%20views%20not%20wanting%20the%20responsibility%20of%20raising%20a%20child%20as%20selfish.%20But%20it's%20our%20choice%2C%20and%20we've%20decided%20that%20there%20are%20things%20in%20our%20lives%20that%20are%20more%20important%20than%20having%20a%20baby.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EI've%20never%20wavered%20about%20not%20having%20children%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWatching%20other%20people%20have%20children%20has%20solidified%20my%20decision.%20When%20I%20see%20the%20work%20that%20goes%20into%20being%20a%20parent%2C%20I%20know%20I%20made%20the%20right%20decision.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20understand%20why%20people%20feel%20strongly%20about%20our%20choice%20because%20I%20do%2C%20too.%20But%20I%20wish%20people%20would%20respect%20our%20decision%20and%20consider%20whether%20it's%20their%20place%20to%20question%20someone%20else's%20choices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20it%20would%20be%20unfair%20to%20bring%20a%20child%20into%20the%20world%20if%20you%20know%20that%20you%20don't%20want%20to%20be%20a%20parent.%20That%20doesn't%20make%20me%20selfish.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennial-dink-who-never-having-kids-selfish-2024-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704451377000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6596e2e46979d73718206643%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennial-dink-who-never-having-kids-selfish-2024-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Jess%20Lorimer%20said%20watching%20her%20friends%20have%20kids%20further%20solidified%20her%20and%20her%20husband's%20decision%20to%20remain%20childless%2C%20but%20people%20can%20be%20critical.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Isabelle%20Aron)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennial-dink-who-never-having-kids-selfish-2024-1%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Paramore%3A%20Rock%20band%20drop%20out%20of%20headline%20slot%20at%20LA%20festival%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704450787000%