n-plagiarism-2024-1%3Ffbclid%3DIwAR3Laqfhht8olfVzyA4GuUTMuPaweiiUiTa6LhJ91QA3NboRj_UbKfcO5o4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehedge%20fund%20manager%20Bill%20Ackman%3C%2Fa%3E%20scored%20a%20victory.%20After%20weeks%20of%20tweeting%20about%20how%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fharvard-president-claudine-gay-to-resign-reports-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHarvard's%20president%2C%20Claudine%20Gay%2C%20should%20step%20down%3C%2Fa%3E%20amid%20plagiarism%20accusations%20and%20fallout%20from%20her%20controversial%20testimony%20at%20a%20congressional%20hearing%20on%20college%20campus%20antisemitism%2C%20she%20did.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20billionaire%20isn't%20done%20giving%20his%20thoughts%20on%20university%20leadership.%20Less%20than%2024%20hours%20after%20Gay's%20resignation%20earlier%20this%20week%2C%20Ackman%20opined%20on%20who%20should%20replace%20her.%20In%20a%2025%2C000-character%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FBillAckman%2Fstatus%2F1742441534627184760%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epost%20on%20X%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20included%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbill-ackman-says-dei-is-racist-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecriticisms%20of%20DEI%20and%20claims%20of%20reverse%20racism%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20he%20suggested%20that%20Harvard%20and%20other%20universities%20%26quot%3Bbroaden%20their%20searches%20to%20include%20capable%20business%20people%20for%20the%20role%20of%20president.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAckman%20likely%20won't%20get%20his%20way%20on%20this%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdvancing%20through%20academia%20to%20the%20role%20of%20president%20is%20still%20the%20traditional%20route%2C%20with%2054%25%20of%20college%20presidents%20in%20the%20US%20taking%20this%20path.%20That's%20according%20to%20the%20American%20Council%20on%20Education's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.acenet.edu%2FResearch-Insights%2FPages%2FAmerican-College-President-Study.aspx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2023%20American%20College%20President%20Study%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20which%20surveyed%20more%20than%201%2C000%20presidents.%20Twenty-eight%20percent%20of%20respondents%20said%20they%20took%20an%20administrative%20pathway%20to%20the%20presidency%20%E2%80%94%20and%20only%204%25%20reported%20taking%20a%20business%20pathway%20to%20their%20role.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%202017%20Deloitte%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww2.deloitte.com%2Fcontent%2Fdam%2Finsights%2Fus%2Farticles%2F3861_Pathways-to-the-university-presidency%2FDUP_Pathways-to-the-university-presidency.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Esurvey%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20sitting%20college%20presidents%20found%20they%20%26quot%3Boverwhelmingly%20agreed%26quot%3B%20that%20campus%20leaders%20need%20academic%20experience.%20Only%2014%25%20would%20have%20seemingly%20agreed%20with%20Ackman%20that%20private%20or%20business%20candidates%20are%20a%20good%20fit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EWhat%20does%20a%20university%20president%20actually%20do%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20people%20aren't%20a%20popular%20choice%20for%20the%20position%20for%20several%20reasons%2C%20many%20of%20which%20have%20to%20do%20with%20a%20president's%20responsibilities.%20Ackman%20doesn't%20get%20entirely%20get%20the%20details%20right%20on%20those.%20According%20to%20the%20hedge%20fund%20manager's%20lengthy%20X%20post%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20president's%20job%20%E2%80%94%20managing%20thousands%20of%20employees%2C%20overseeing%20a%20%2450%20billion%20endowment%2C%20raising%20money%2C%20managing%20expenses%2C%20capital%20allocation%2C%20real%20estate%20acquisition%2C%20disposition%2C%20and%20construction%2C%20and%20reputation%20management%20%E2%80%94%20are%20responsibilities%20that%20few%20career%20academics%20are%20capable%20of%20executing.%26quot%3B%20He%20went%20on%20to%20criticize%20the%20performance%20of%20Harvard's%20endowment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20most%20recent%20fiscal%20year%2C%20which%20ended%20on%20June%C2%A030%2C%202023%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hmc.harvard.edu%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FFY23_HMC_Annual_Report.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20endowment%20returned%202.9%25%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20value%20stood%20at%20%2450.7%20billion.%20According%20to%20Bloomberg%20data%2C%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20returned%20just%20under%2020%25%20in%20the%20same%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20reality%2C%20a%20number%20of%20the%20responsibilities%20named%20by%20Ackman%20are%20delegated%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0particularly%20the%20financial%20ones.%20For%20example%2C%20a%20university%20president%20doesn't%20actually%20oversee%20a%20school's%20endowment.%20That%20job%20is%20contracted%20out%20to%20money%20managers%2C%20said%20Benjamin%20Ginsberg%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20Johns%20Hopkins%20University%20and%20author%20of%20%26quot%3BThe%20Fall%20of%20the%20Faculty%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20book%20about%20the%20growing%20role%20of%20administrators%20on%20college%20campuses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20the%20endowment%20doesn't%20do%20well%2C%20it's%20not%20the%20fault%20of%20the%20faculty%2C%26quot%3B%20Ginsberg%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BHarvard's%20endowment%20is%20a%20classic%20underperformer%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20and%20it's%20professionally%20managed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20while%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funiversity-president-fundraising-penn-liz-magill-resigning-harvard-claudine-gay-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Efundraising%20is%20an%20important%20part%20of%20a%20college%20president's%20job%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20there%20is%20no%20reason%20a%20charismatic%20president%20%E2%80%94%20a%20Nobel%20prize%20winner%2C%20for%20example%2C%20or%20a%20lauded%20legal%20scholar%20%E2%80%94%20and%20a%20well-connected%20board%20of%20trustees%20can't%20drum%20up%20support.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAckman%20also%20leaves%20out%20a%20key%20responsibility%20of%20un