poor%20and%20very%20unequal%20country%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESUV%20sales%20in%20India%20are%20rising%20while%20sales%20of%20entry%20level%20cars%20and%20two-wheelers%20are%20shrinking%20or%20lower%20than%20pre-Covid%20times%3B%20should%20recent%20statistics%20like%20this%20surprise%20us%2C%20still%3F%20While%20the%20government%20would%20like%20India%E2%80%99s%20citizens%20to%20believe%20that%20India%20came%20out%20of%20the%20Covid%20exogenous%20shock%20in%20a%20V-shaped%20recovery%2C%20and%20has%20become%20the%20fastest%20growing%20large%20economy%20in%20the%20world%2C%20most%20economists%20outside%20of%20government%20have%20repeatedly%20argued%20what%20India%20experienced%20has%20been%20a%20K-shaped%20rebound%20(not%20recovery).%20Could%20these%20kinds%20of%20data%20be%20behind%20the%20fact%20that%20suddenly%20India%20became%20the%20fifth%C2%A0largest%20economy%20in%20the%20world%2C%20overtaking%20the%20UK%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20300px)%2085vw%2C%20300px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F03150954%2FPrism.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22300%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F03150954%2FPrism.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F03150954%2FPrism-150x150.png%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-691446%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22300%5C%22%3EThere%20are%20many%20dimensions%20to%20this%20K-shaped%20recovery.%20First%2C%20the%20stock%20market%20continued%20to%20boom%20through%20much%20of%20Covid%2C%20while%20the%20real%20economy%20was%20tanking%2C%20clearly%20benefitting%20the%20minuscule%20minority%20who%20benefit%20from%20investing%20in%20stocks%20and%20bonds.%20A%20second%20dimension%20of%20the%20K-shaped%20recovery%20was%20that%20listed%20company%20profits%20rose%20to%20a%20seven-year%20high%2C%20real%20wages%20shrank%20and%20jobs%20shrank.%20A%20third%20dimension%20was%20that%20the%20organised%2C%20formal%20sectors%20of%20the%20economy%20generally%20performed%20well%2C%20despite%20the%20shock%2C%20except%20for%20a%20limited%20period%20of%20time%2C%20while%20the%20unorganised%20sector%20was%20already%20reeling%20from%20consecutive%20shocks%20inflicted%20by%20the%20government%20by%20one%20policy%20mistake%20after%20another%20(demonetisation%2C%20badly%20planned%20Goods%20and%20Services%20Tax%20in%20July%202017%2C%20and%20then%20a%20lockdown%20of%20the%20entire%20economy%20and%20workforce%20at%20four%20hours%20notice%20in%20March%202020%20when%20there%20were%20less%20than%20600%20Covid%20cases%2C%20needlessly%20strict%20and%20national%20in%20scope).%20The%20unorganised%20and%20MSME%20sectors%20have%20barely%20recovered%20from%20the%20multiple%20shocks%20in%20succession%20%E2%80%93%20which%20is%20why%20joblessness%20remains%20at%20a%2050-year%20high.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20fourth%20dimension%20of%20the%20K-shaped%20recovery%20was%20the%20less%20well%20known%20facet%20that%2045%20million%20joined%20agriculture%20in%202020%2C%20and%20an%20additional%20seven%20million%20were%20added%20to%20the%20farm%20workforce%20in%202021%2C%20during%20the%20first%20and%20second%20wave%20reverse%20migrations.%20Even%20in%202022%20(according%20to%20the%20latest%20Periodic%20Labour%20Force%20Survey%202021-22)%2C%20the%20absolute%20number%20of%20workers%20in%20agriculture%20has%20not%20fallen.%20These%20increases%20in%20farm%20workforce%20totally%20reversed%20a%2015-year%20trend%2C%20which%20saw%20an%20absolute%20decline%20in%20farm%20workforce%20since%202004%2C%20a%20first%20in%20post%20independence%20history).%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20manufacturing%20employment%20has%20not%20risen%2C%20and%20has%20stagnated.%20So%20the%20entire%20process%20of%20structural%20change%20that%20had%20gathered%20momentum%20between%202004%20and%202014%2C%20when%20the%20economy%20grew%20at%208%25%20per%20year%2C%20an%20unprecedented%20phenomenon%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20post%20independence%20history%2C%20has%20not%20only%20been%20stalled%2C%20it%20has%20aborted%20and%20been%20reversed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22What%20Do%20We%20Really%20Know%20About%20India's%20GDP%3F%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fwhat-do-we-really-know-about-indias-gdp%5C%22%3EWhat%20Do%20We%20Really%20Know%20About%20India%E2%80%99s%20GDP%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20joblessness%20rose%2C%20consumption%20demand%20has%20fallen%20or%20stagnated.%20In%20FY%202022-23%2C%20the%20Second%20Advance%20Estimates%20for%20GDP%20released%20February%202023%20suggest%20that%20per%20capita%20consumption%2C%20on%20average%2C%20has%20risen%20slightly%20above%20the%202019%20level.%20Inevitably%2C%20with%20incomes%20stagnant%2C%20the%20household%20savings%20to%20GDP%20ratio%20has%20fallen%20in%20recent%20years%3B%20people%20are%20maintaining%20consumption%20by%20dissaving.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20there%20were%20plenty%20in%20the%20top%20end%20of%20the%20middle%20class%20and%20the%20upper%20classes%20who%2C%20during%20Covid%2C%20were%20not%20eating%20out%2C%20not%20travelling%2C%20not%20going%20on%20holidays%20in%20India%20or%20abroad%2C%20and%20hence%20were%20saving%20more%2C%20and%20could%20now%20splurge%20on%20SUVs%20or%20more%20expensive%20cars.%20Meanwhile%2C%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20the%20population%2C%20seriously%20impacted%20by%20joblessness%2C%20stagnant%20wages%20and%20consistently%20high%20inflation%2C%20fuelled%20by%20government%20taxes%20on%20petrol%2C%20diesel%20and%20cooking%20gas%2C%20which%20are%20inputs%20into%20both%20production%20of%20goods%20and%20services%2C%20has%20less%20disposable%20income%20left%20over%20to%20buy%20such%20luxuries%20as%20motor%20vehicles%2C%20whether%20two%20wheelers%20or%20small%20cars.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EViral%20Acharya%2C%20former%20deputy%20governor%20of%20the%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20India%20and%20professor%20at%20the%20Stern%20School%20of%20Business%2C%20NYU%2C%20wrote%20in%20a%20recent%20academic%20paper%20that%20India%E2%80%99s%20biggest%20five%20firms%E2%80%99%20share%20in%20total%20assets%20of%20the%20non-financial%20sectors%20rose%20from%2010%25%20in%201991%20to%20nearly%2018%25%20in%202021%2C%20whereas%20the%20share%20of%20the%20next%20Big%205%20business%20groups%20fell%20from%2018%25%20in%201992%20to%20less%20than%209%25.%20This%20growth%20has%20been%20biggest%20in%20the%20last%20decade.%20%E2%80%9CIn%20other%20words%2C%20Big%205%20grew%20not%20just%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20the%20smallest%20firms%2C%20but%20also%20of%20the%20next%20largest%20firms%2C%E2%80%9D%20Acharya%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Big%205%20industrial%20groups%20referred%20to%20in%20the%20paper%20are%20the%20Mukesh%20Ambani-helmed%20Reliance%20Group%2C%20Tata%20Group%2C%20Aditya%20Birla%20Group%2C%20Adani%20Group%20and%20Bharti%20Telecom.%20He%20said%20the%20growth%20of%20such%20conglomerates%20raises%20several%20concerns%20%E2%80%93%20like%20the%20risk%20of%20crony%20capitalism%2C%20related%20party%20transactions%20within%20their%20byzantine%20corporate%20organisation%20charts%2C%20and%20over-leveraging%20due%20to%20an%20implicit%20too-big-to-fail%20perception%2C%20among%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESantosh%20Mehrotra%20is%20Professorial%20Fellow%2C%20Nehru%20Memorial%20Museum%20and%20Library%2C%20New%20Delhi%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704447018000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F05124611%2Fandrea-leopardi-B4qmgZdSQp0-unsplash.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fwhat-we-know-about-indias-post-covid-economy-recovery-and-rising-inequality%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22While%20the%20upper%20and%20upper%20middle%20classes%20saved%20money%20during%20the%20pandemic%20that%20they%20are%20spending%20on%20luxury%20goods%2C%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20the%20population%20has%20been%20seriously%20impacted%20by%2