h%20a%20silver%20hair%20transformation%20for%20a%20fan%20meeting.%20The%20actor%20reveals%20that%20he%20decided%20to%20bleach%20his%20hair%20without%20any%20particular%20reason%2C%20simply%20because%20he%20was%20tired%20of%20black%20hair.%20The%20new%20silver%20hair%20color%20is%20described%20as%20mysterious%2C%20with%20a%20mix%20of%20silver%2C%20gold%2C%20and%20blue%20that%20changes%20depending%20on%20the%20light.%20In%20addition%20to%20his%20recent%20projects%2C%20including%20'Tale%20of%20the%20Nine%20Tailed'%20and%20'Single%20in%20Seoul'%2C%20Lee%20Dong%20Wook%20has%20upcoming%20projects%20such%20as%20the%20thriller%20drama%20'A%20Shop%20for%20Killers'%20and%20the%20TV%20series%20'The%20Good%20Man'.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fweb-series%2Fnews%2Fkorean%2Flee-dong-wook-reveals-the-real-reason-why-he-dyed-his-hair-silver%2Farticleshow%2F106570821.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%225%20Potential%20Trouble%20Spots%20That%20Could%20Knock%20the%20Global%20Economy%20Off%20Course%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20global%20economy%20was%20tested%20in%202023%20as%20it%20rarely%20has%20been%20before%3A%20inflation%20and%20the%20most%20aggressive%20monetary%20tightening%20campaign%20in%20decades%2C%20wars%20in%20Europe%20and%20the%20Middle%20East%2C%20a%20festering%20real%20estate%20crisis%20in%20China%20and%20the%20deepening%20rivalry%20between%20Washington%20and%20Beijing%2C%20which%20is%20forcing%20companies%20to%20rethink%20supply%20chains%20and%20security.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20these%20pain%20points%2C%20the%20post-pandemic%20global%20recovery%20managed%20to%20roll%20on.%20In%20the%20US%20consumers%20defied%20expectations%20and%20kept%20spending%2C%20prompting%20many%20economists%20to%20ditch%20their%20downside%20scenarios%20and%20forecast%20a%20rare%20soft%20landing.%20In%20China%20the%20booming%20electric-vehicle%20industry-along%20with%20a%20healthy%20dose%20of%20fiscal%20stimulus-helped%20leaders%20stick%20close%20to%20their%20growth%20target.%20And%20the%20world%20economy's%20great%20new%20hope%2C%20India%2C%20took%20up%20some%20of%20the%20slack.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20International%20Monetary%20Fund%20forecasts%20global%20growth%20of%202.9%25%20in%202024%2C%20a%20whisker%20below%20last%20year.%20With%20two%20wars%20raging%20and%20some%2040%20national%20elections%20on%20the%20calendar%2C%20political%20developments%20will%20shape%20the%20year%2C%20especially%20as%20Donald%20Trump%20makes%20a%20go%20at%20winning%20back%20the%20presidency.%20But%20crucial%20economic%20stress%20points%20could%20upend%20the%20benign%20outlook.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWill%20the%20American%20Consumer%20Capitulate%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20a%20blockbuster%202023%2C%20the%20US%20economy%20is%20expected%20to%20come%20back%20to%20earth%20in%20the%20coming%2012%20months.%20Whether%20that's%20a%20recession%20or%20a%20soft%20landing%20will%20depend%20in%20good%20part%20on%20how%20the%20job%20market%20holds%20up.%20So%20far%20it's%20shrugged%20off%20the%20Federal%20Reserve's%20barrage%20of%20interest-rate%20increases%2C%20but%20this%20year%20could%20see%20an%20inflection%20point%20even%20though%20policymakers%20have%20signaled%20they're%20done%20hiking.%20An%20uptick%20in%20unemployment%20would%20hit%20consumer%20spending%2C%20which%20in%20the%20US%20accounts%20for%20almost%20two-thirds%20of%20economic%20output.%20The%20Fed's%20latest%20projections%20see%20the%20jobless%20rate%20climbing%20to%204.1%25%20by%20the%20end%20of%20the%20year.%20Unemployment%20claims%2C%20published%20weekly%2C%20are%20a%20leading%20indicator%20of%20labor%20market%20softness%20and%20therefore%20merit%20watching.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECan%20Beijing%20Keep%20a%20Lid%20on%20the%20Housing%20Crisis%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20world's%20second-biggest%20economy%20is%20in%20the%20midst%20of%20a%20multiyear%20slowdown%2C%20triggered%20in%20part%20by%20President%20Xi%20Jinping's%20crackdown%20on%20real%20estate%20speculation.%20Developers%20are%20saddled%20with%20vast%20portfolios%20of%20%26quot%3Brotten%20tails%26quot%3B-apartments%20that%20were%20bought%20but%20never%20built.%20Nomura%20Securities%20Co.%20estimates%20that%20some%2020%20million%20units%20were%20presold%20for%20which%20construction%20has%20been%20delayed%20or%20hasn't%20started.%20Those%20waiting%20for%20their%20new%20apartments%20are%20becoming%20increasingly%20impatient%2C%20turning%20the%20issue%20into%20a%20potential%20threat%20to%20social%20stability.%20Top%20officials%20have%20pledged%20to%20prevent%20a%20cascade%20of%20debt%20defaults%20by%20developers-a%20disaster%20that%20would%20engulf%20the%20banking%20sector%20and%20potentially%20doom%20China%20to%20a%20Japan-like%20lost%20decade%20of%20anemic%20growth.%20This%20may%20be%20the%20year%20that%20the%20slow%20drip%20of%20government%20measures%20gives%20way%20to%20a%20full-blown%20bailout.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEuropean%20Laggard%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGermany%20was%20the%20worst%20performer%20among%20major%20economies%20in%202023.%20High%20energy%20prices%20and%20tight%20monetary%20policy%2C%20coupled%20with%20weaker%20global%20demand%20for%20its%20exports%2C%20caused%20a%20slight%20contraction%20in%20gross%20domestic%20product%20for%20the%20year.%20There's%20no%20shortage%20of%20problems%20going%20into%202024%2C%20including%20the%20ongoing%20war%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20an%20auto%20industry%20facing%20intense%20competition%20from%20Chinese-made%20EVs%20and%20tighter%20controls%20on%20government%20spending.%20The%20country's%20world-beating%20manufacturing%20sector%20must%20contend%20with%20a%20costly%20and%20politically%20fraught%20transition%20to%20alternate%20forms%20of%20energy%20after%20losing%20access%20to%20cheap%20gas%20piped%20in%20from%20Russia%2C%20as%20well%20as%20a%20reshuffling%20of%20supply%20chains%20in%20response%20to%20a%20US-led%20effort%20to%20contain%20China.%20For%20a%20read%20on%20whether%20the%20malaise%20is%20easing%20or%20deepening%2C%20watch%20the%20Ifo%20Institute's%20index%20of%20business%20expectations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJapan's%20Risky%20Exit%20From%20Negative%20Rates%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20country's%20decades-long%20experiment%20with%20unorthodox%20monetary%20policies%20is%20nearing%20its%20final%20chapter.%20The%20yawning%20gap%20between%20yields%20of%20Japanese%20and%20US%20government%20bonds%20in%20November%20helped%20drive%20the%20yen%20to%20its%20lowest%20level%20since%20the%20early%201990s%2C%20pushing%20up%20the%20cost%20of%20imported%20fuel%20and%20food%20and%20eating%20into%20purchasing%20power.%20With%20inflation%20hovering%20above%20the%20Bank%20of%20Japan's%202%25%20target%20for%20more%20than%20a%20year%20and%20a%20half%2C%20Governor%20Kazuo%20Ueda%20is%20widely%20expected%20to%20abandon%20the%20world's%20last%20remaining%20negative%20interest%20rate%20as%20he%20inches%20away%20from%20the%20yield%20curve%20control%20framework%20he%20inherited%20from%20his%20predecessor.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe'll%20have%20to%20tread%20carefully.%20For%20a%20generation%2C%20pension%20funds%2C%20insurers%2C%20banks%20and%20even%20mom%20and%20pop%20investors%20have%20parked%20their%20money%20in%20assets%20overseas%20to%20earn%20some%20interest%2C%20making%20Japan%20the%20world's%20top%20creditor%20nation.%20If%20Japanese%20government%20bonds%20start%20to%20offer%20better%20returns%2C%20trillions%20of%20yen%20could%20rush%20back%20home%2C%20causing%20immense%20disruption%20to%20global%20financial%20markets.%20For%20Ueda%2C%20moving%20too%20quickly%20risks%20snuffing%20out%20the%20long-sought%20return%20of%20sustainable%20price%20rises.%20Too%20slow%2C%20and%20the%20markets%20may%20be%20emboldened%20to%20test%20the%20BOJ's%20resolve%20to%20maintain%20yield%20levels-risking%20an%20even%20sharper%20dive%20for%20the%20yen.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECan%20India%20Live%20Up%20to%20Its%20Promise%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20China%20settles%20into%20a%20slower%20growth%20track%2C%20economists%20are%20looking%20to%20India%20to%20eventually%20take%20over%20as%20the%20new%20global%20growth%20engine.%20It's%20a%20lot%20to%20live%20up%20to%2C%20and%20with%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20facing%20an%20election%20sometime%20in%20April%20or%20May%2C%20politics%20will%20add%20to%20the%20challenge.%20Goldman%20Sachs%20Group%20Inc.%20economists%20expect%20increased%20government%20spending%20to%20be%20the%20main%20growth%20driver%20going%20into%20the%20vote%2C%20with%20private-sector%20investment%20taking%20over%20in%20the%20second%20half%20of%20the%20year.%20Yet%20while%20India%20has%20been%20growing%20faster%20than%20just%20about%20any%20other%20major%20economy%2C%20the%20unemployment%20rate%20climbed%20above%2010%25%20in%20October%2C%20the%20highest%20in%20two%20years%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Centre%20for%20Monitoring%20Indian%20Economy.%20What's%20more%2C%20the%20labor%20participation%20rate%20for%20women%20is%20stuck%20below%2060%25.%20Economists%20at%20HSBC%20Holdings%20Plc%20say%20that%20even%20if%20economic%20growth%20can%20accelerate%20to%207.5%25%20per%20year%20over%20the%20next%20decade%2C%20only%20about%2045%20million%20of%20the%2070%20million%20jobs%20needed%20to%20match%20India's%20growing%20population%20will%20be%20created%2C%20leaving%2025%20million%20people%20behind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704445380000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-10%2Fakklhcg_indian-economy-reuters_625x300_03_October_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fgreat-new-hope-india-and-4-others-on-economists-radar-in-2024-4804007%2