ses%20reportedly%20received%20payments%20totalling%20at%20least%20%247.8%20million%20directly%20from%20at%20least%2020%20foreign%20governments%2C%20including%20India%2C%20as%20per%20a%20report%20released%20by%20Democrat%20members%20of%20the%20US%20House%20Oversight%20Committee%20on%20Thursday%2C%20January%204.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAccording%20to%20the%20report%20%E2%80%98%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Foversightdemocrats.house.gov%2Fsites%2Fdemocrats.oversight.house.gov%2Ffiles%2F2024-01-04.COA%2520DEMS%2520-%2520Mazars%2520Report.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EWhite%20House%20for%20Sale%3A%20How%20Princes%2C%20Prime%20Ministers%2C%20and%20Premiers%20Paid%20Off%20President%20Trump%E2%80%99%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3Eby%20House%20Oversight%20Committee%20Democrats%2C%20the%20payments%20are%20only%20a%20tiny%20portion%20of%20the%20foreign%20payments%20directed%20to%20Trump%20and%20his%20family%20throughout%20his%202017-2021%20administration.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThese%20records%20listed%20the%20payments%20for%20two%20years%20at%20four%20out%20of%20Trump%E2%80%99s%20500%20businesses%20%E2%80%93%20Trump%20International%20Hotel%20in%20Washington%20DC%2C%20Trump%20International%20Hotel%20in%20Las%20Vegas%2C%20Trump%20Tower%20on%20Fifth%20Avenue%20in%20New%20York%20and%20Trump%20World%20Tower%20at%20845%20United%20Nations%20Plaza%20in%20New%20York.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20US%20constitution%20forbids%20federal%20officeholders%20from%20accepting%20any%20form%20of%20money%2C%20payments%2C%20or%20gifts%20from%20foreign%20governments%20and%20monarchs%20without%20obtaining%20the%20consent%20of%20Congress.%20The%20report%2C%20drafted%20by%20the%20Democrats%2C%20highlights%20that%20Trump%20did%20not%20seek%20any%20such%20consent%20from%20Congress.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20majority%20of%20the%20documented%20%247.8%20million%20comes%20from%20the%20Chinese%20government%2C%20with%20a%20significant%20portion%20of%20%245.5%20million%20originating%20from%20sources%20such%20as%20the%20Chinese%20embassy%2C%20the%20state-run%20Industrial%20and%20Commercial%20Bank%20of%20China%20(ICBC)%2C%20and%20Hainan%20Airlines%20Holding%20Company.%20These%20details%20were%20extracted%20from%20documents%20acquired%20from%20Trump%E2%80%99s%20former%20accounting%20firm%2C%20Mazars%2C%20and%20the%20US%20Securities%20and%20Exchange%20Commission.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EChina%20outspent%20the%20second%20highest%20spender%2C%20Saudi%20Arabia%2C%20by%20over%20nine%20times.%20Other%20countries%20mentioned%20in%20the%20report%20include%20Qatar%2C%20the%20United%20Arab%20Emirates%2C%20Malaysia%2C%20Kuwait%2C%20and%20the%20Philippines.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%20secured%20the%20fifth%20position%2C%20having%20spent%20a%20total%20of%20%24282%2C764%20at%20Trump%20World%20Tower%20in%20New%20York%20and%20Trump%20International%20Hotel%20in%20the%20US%20capital%20of%20Washington%20D.C.%20from%202017%20to%202020.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESpecifically%2C%20the%20India%20chapter%E2%80%99s%20table%20provided%20a%20detailed%20breakdown%20of%20the%20amount%2C%20disclosing%20that%20the%20Permanent%20Mission%20of%20India%20to%20the%20UN%20allocated%20%24264%2C184%20for%20payments%20to%20Trump%20World%20Tower%20from%202017%20to%202020.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20has%20been%20no%20official%20response%20from%20the%20Indian%20government.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F05122344%2Fdownload.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22297%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-691717%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22447%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20Trump%20World%20Tower%20in%20New%20York.%20Photo%3A%20Evan%20Joseph%20Images%2Fwww.trump.com%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20it%20is%20not%20mentioned%20in%20the%20report%2C%20the%20Trump%20World%20Tower%2C%20which%20is%20located%20opposite%20the%20UN%20headquarters%2C%20had%20been%20the%20official%20residence%20of%20the%20India%E2%80%99s%20Permanent%20Ambassador%20since%20India%20bought%20a%20unit%20in%202004%2C%20%3Cem%3EThe%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EWire%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20learnt.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20limited%20records%20shared%20by%20Trump%E2%80%99s%20accounting%20firm%2C%20Mazars%20stated%20that%20India%20had%20spent%20%2466%2C046%20on%20combined%20common%20charges%20for%20two%20units%20at%20Trump%20World%20Tower%20on%20Turtle%20Bay%20in%202018.%20The%20report%20then%20projects%20this%20figure%20over%20the%20four%20years%20of%20Trump%E2%80%99s%20presidency%2C%20resulting%20in%20an%20estimated%20total%20of%20%24264%2C184.%20It%20also%20said%20that%20this%20figure%20did%20not%20include%20additional%20charges%20like%20that%20of%20electricity%20and%20special%20assessment%20which%20were%20paid%20in%202018.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20remaining%20%2418%2C500%20was%20apparently%20the%20expenditure%20by%20the%20Indian%20embassy%20in%20Washington%20DC%20on%20three%20separate%20stays%20by%20Indian%20diplomats%20during%20February%20and%20March%202017.%20These%20days%20correspond%20with%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FAroonDeep%2Fstatus%2F966853259041308673%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Edetails%20of%20stay%20obtained%20by%20an%20Indian%20journalist%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20under%20Right%20to%20Information%20Act%20of%20the%20stay%20of%20eight%20Indian%20officials%20in%202018.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20India%20section%20observed%20the%20South%20Asian%20country%20was%20home%20to%20the%20largest%20number%20of%20Trump-owned%20business%20projects%20outside%20the%20United%20States.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CFormer%20President%20Trump%E2%80%99s%20numerous%20foreign%20business%20entanglements%20in%20India%20and%20his%20direction%20of%20U.S.%20foreign%20policy%20during%20his%20presidency%20repeatedly%20intersected%2C%20creating%20conspicuous%20conflicts%20of%20interest%E2%80%9D%2C%20said%20the%20report%20by%20the%20Democrats%20on%20the%20Oversight%20Committee.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20stated%20that%20Trump%20laid%20the%20foundation%20for%20his%20%E2%80%9Cuniquely%20warm%20relationship%E2%80%9D%20with%20the%20Indian%20Prime%20Minster%20Narendra%20Modi%20through%20his%20business%20ventures%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20fact%2C%20while%20visiting%20the%20White%20House%20during%20President%20Trump%E2%80%99s%20Administration%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi%20explicitly%20remarked%20that%20Mr.%20Trump%20had%20been%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.presidency.ucsb.edu%2Fdocuments%2Fremarks-prior-meeting-with-prime-minister-narendra-modi-india%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Efull%20of%20very%20warm%20remarks%20and%20observations%20for%20me%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9D%20when%20Mr%20Trump%20had%20previously%20been%20in%20India%20promoting%20his%20business%20interests%20prior%20to%20his%20presidency%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20stated.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20300px)%2085vw%2C%20300px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F05122545%2Fdownload-1.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22300%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F05122545%2Fdownload-1.jpeg%20225w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F05122545%2Fdownload-1-150x150.jpeg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-691718%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22299%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EMangal%20Prabhat%20Lodha.%20Photo%3A%2