Cp%3E%26quot%3BPart%20of%20what%20makes%20her%20human%20is%20that%20she%20makes%20mistakes%2C%20owns%20them%2C%20and%20apologizes%20when%20appropriate%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FBillAckman%2Fstatus%2F1742996414316101736%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epost%20on%20X%3C%2Fa%3E%20following%20Business%20Insider's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbill-ackman-wife-neri-oxman-mit-dissertation-plagiarism-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%20on%20Oxman's%20plagiarism%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20a%20starkly%20different%20approach%20than%20the%20one%20he%20took%20toward%20Gay%20after%20she%20stepped%20down%20earlier%20this%20week.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20Ackman%20said%20she%20should%20be%20fired%20from%20Harvard's%20faculty%20entirely%20due%20to%20what%20he%20called%20%26quot%3Bserious%20plagiarism%20issues.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BStudents%20are%20forced%20to%20withdraw%20for%20much%20less%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20posted%20on%20X.%20%26quot%3BRewarding%20her%20with%20a%20highly%20paid%20faculty%20position%20sets%20a%20very%20bad%20precedent%20for%20academic%20integrity%20at%20Harvard.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20examples%20seen%20of%20Oxman%20and%20Gay's%20plagiarism%20have%20more%20similarities%20than%20differences%2C%20according%20to%20experts%20and%20an%20internal%20analysis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGay%20was%20accused%2C%20accurately%20in%20at%20least%20some%20of%20the%20cases%2C%20of%20using%20verbatim%20text%20from%20outside%20sources%20and%2C%20though%20in%20most%20cases%20the%20source%20was%20cited%2C%20it%20was%20not%20marked%20as%20quoted%20text%2C%26quot%3B%20Jonathan%20Bailey%2C%20a%20plagiarism%20expert%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BThat%20seems%20to%20be%20pretty%20much%20what%20happened%20here%20with%20Oxman.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20authors%20made%20mistakes%20in%20their%20papers%2C%20Bailey%20said%2C%20but%20a%20handful%20of%20improper%20citations%20found%20in%20a%20research%20paper%20or%20dissertation%20spanning%20a%20couple%20hundred%20pages%20would%20not%20typically%20rise%20to%20the%20level%20of%20termination%20in%20academia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20kind%20of%20plagiarism%20%26quot%3Busually%20comes%20not%20so%20much%20from%20a%20malicious%20intent%20to%20steal%2C%20but%20from%20a%20very%2C%20very%20soppy%20writing%20style%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20how%20the%20two%20stack%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ENeither%20Oxman%20nor%20Gay%20are%20accused%20of%20stealing%20big%20ideas%20%E2%80%94%20but%20their%20works%20do%20contain%20citation%20inadequacies%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20main%20issue%20for%20both%20Gay%20and%20Oxman%20has%20to%20do%20with%20quotation%20marks%3A%20The%20two%20included%20direct%20passages%20cribbed%20from%20other%20academics%2C%20and%20while%20they%20cited%20their%20sources%20in%20line%20and%20included%20the%20sources%20in%20their%20bibliographies%2C%20the%20passages%20were%20not%20put%20in%20quotes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBelow%20is%20a%20passage%20from%20a%20paper%20by%20Israeli%20scholars%20Steve%20Weiner%20and%20H.%20Daniel%20Wagner%20alongside%20a%20passage%20from%20Oxman's%20dissertation%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22comp%20wiener%20and%20wanger%20and%20oxman%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F659722991c5c7b8c9a0e1e12%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222072%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EA%20similar%20comparison%2C%20first%20identified%20by%20Christopher%20Rufo%2C%20a%20conservative%20activist%2C%20and%20Christopher%20Brunet%2C%20a%20contributing%20editor%20at%20The%20American%20Conservative%2C%20shows%20Gay%20failing%20to%20put%20quotation%20marks%20around%20a%20passage%20from%20Lawrence%20Bobo%20and%20Franklin%20D.%20Gilliam's%20%26quot%3BRace%2C%20Sociopolitical%20Participation%2C%20and%20Black%20Empowerment%26quot%3B%20in%20her%201997%20Harvard%20dissertation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3E%26quot%3BThe%20results%20show%20that%20blacks%20in%20high-black-empowerment%20areas-as%20indicated%20by%20control%20of%20the%20mayor's%20office-are%20more%20active%20than%20either%20blacks%20living%20in%20low-empowerment%20areas%20or%20their%20white%20counterparts%20of%20comparable%20socioeconomic%20status.%20Furthermore%2C%20the%20results%20show%20that%20empowerment%20influences%20black%20participation%20by%20contributing%20to%20a%20more%20trusting%20and%20efficacious%20orientation%20to%20politics%20and%20by%20greatly%20increasing%20black%20attentiveness%20to%20political%20affairs.%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20%3Cem%3ELawrence%20Bobo%20and%20Franklin%20D.%20Gilliam%2C%20Jr.%20in%20%26quot%3BRace%2C%20Sociopolitical%20Participation%2C%20and%20Black%20Empowerment%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3E%26quot%3BUsing%201987%20survey%20data%2C%20Bobo%20and%20Gilliam%20found%20that%20African-Americans%20in%20%26quot%3Bhigh%20black-empowerment%26quot%3B%20areas%E2%80%94as%20indicated%20by%20control%20of%20the%20mayor's%20office%E2%80%94are%20more%20active%20than%20either%20African-Americans%20in%20low%20empowerment%20areas%20or%20their%20white%20counterparts%20of%20comparable%20socioeconomic%20status.%20Empowerment%2C%20they%20conclude%2C%20influences%20black%20participation%20by%20contributing%20to%20a%20more%20trusting%20and%20efficacious%20orientation%20towards%20politics%20and%20by%20greatly%20increasing%20black%20attentiveness%20to%20political%20affairs.%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20%3Cem%3EClaudine%20Gay%20in%20%26quot%3BTaking%20Charge%3A%20Black%20Electoral%20Success%20and%20the%20Redefinition%20of%20American%20Policies%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20omitting%20quotation%20marks%20violated%20MIT's%20academic%20integrity%20code%20at%20the%20time%20of%20Oxman's%20dissertation%20and%20is%20against%20Harvard's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fusingsources.fas.harvard.edu%2Fharvard-plagiarism-policy%23%3A~%3Atext%3DStudents%2520who%252C%2520for%2520whatever%2520reason%2Cto%2520withdraw%2520from%2520the%2520College.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecurrent%20policy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20experts%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0including%20scholars%20whose%20work%20Gay%20and%20Oxman%20copied%20%E2%80%94%20have%20largely%20agreed%20the%20offense%20is%20inconsequential.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20researchers%20make%20this%20type%20of%20mistake%2C%20a%20typical%20course%20of%20action%20might%20be%20to%20issue%20a%20correction%20and%20perhaps%20take%20a%20remedial%20course%20on%20research%20writing%2C%20Bailey%2C%20the%20plagiarism%20expert%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20Gay%20and%20for%20Oxman%2C%20there's%20no%20real%20pattern%20to%20what%20sentence%20is%20used%2C%26quot%3B%20Bailey%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20both%20of%20these%20cases%20could%20be%20a%20case%20where%20the%20author%20pulled%20text%20and%20forgot%20to%20put%20it%20in%20quotes%20or%20intended%20to%20paraphrase%20but%20forgot%20to%20do%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGay%20requested%20several%20corrections%20to%20her%20papers%20after%20the%20citation%20errors%20were%20highlighted%20in%20December.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHarvard's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fharvard-says-president-claudine-gay-did-not-violate-plagiarism-rules-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eboard%20cleared%20Gay%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20%26quot%3Bresearch%20misconduct.%26quot%3B%20In%20an%20op-ed%20published%20in%20The%20New%20York%20Times%20following%20her%20resignation%2C%20Gay%20stood%20by%20her%20work.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20have%20never%20misrepresented%20my%20research%20findings%2C%20nor%20have%20I%20ever%20claimed%20credit%20for%20the%20research%20of%20others%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BMoreover%2C%20the%20citation%20errors%20should%20not%20obscure%20a%20fundamental%20truth%3A%20I%20proudly%20stand%20by%20my%20work%20and%20its%20impact%20on%20the%20field.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20BI's%20report%2C%20Oxman%20apologized%20in%20a%20post%20on%20X%20and%20said%20she%20plans%20to%20%26quot%3Brequest%20that%20MIT%20make%20any%20necessary%20corrections.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnne%20R.%20Williamson%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20Miami%20University%20whose%20work%20was%20improperly%20cited%20by%20Gay%20in%20a%202017%20article%2C%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thecrimson.com%2Farticle%2F2023%2F12%2F15%2Fgay-corrections-plagiarism-allegations%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Harvard%20Crimson%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20an%20email%20that%20she%20was%20%26quot%3Bcompletely%20satisfied%26quot%3B%20with%20Gay's%20subsequent%20correction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPedar%20Anker%2C%20who%20had%20a%20passage%20of%20text%20used%20by%20Oxman%20without%20quotations%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20he%20had%20the%20%26quot%3Bdeepest%20respect%26quot%3B%20for%20Oxman%20and%20that%20it%20was%20an%20%26quot%3Bhonor%26quot%3B%20to%20be%20quoted%20by%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHaving%20said%20that%2C%20the%20quotation%20is%20from%20a%20pedantic%20point%20of%20view%20incorrect%2C%20and%20she%20has%20publicly%20apologized%20for%20that%20on%20X%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BRest%20assured%20that%20her%20apology%20is%20accepted.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECarol%20Swain%2C%20a%20former%20Vanderbilt%20University%20professor%2C%20did%2C%20however%2C%20express%20dismay%20at%20Gay's%20mistakes%20and%20admonished%20her%20and%20Harvard%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2Fclaudine-gay-and-my-scholarship-plagiarism-elite-system-unearned-position-24e4a1b1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EWall%20Street%20Journal%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20op-ed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMs.%20Gay's%20damage%20to%20me%20is%20aggravated%20because%20her%20early%20work%20was%20in%20the%20area%20where%20my%20research%20is%20considered%20seminal.%20Her%20scholarship%20on%20black%20congressional%20representation%2C%20electoral%20districting%20and%20descriptive%20representation%20builds%20on%20terrain%20where%20I%20plowed%20the%20ground%2C%26quot%3B%20Swain%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EBoth%20Oxman%20and%20Gay%20copied%20language%20almost%20word-for-word%2C%20without%20any%20citation%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20her%20330-page%20dissertation%2C%20Oxman%20pulled%20a%20paragraph%2C%20almost%20word-for-word%2C%20from%20a%20book%20published%20in%201998%20by%20German%20physicist%20Claus%20Mattheck%20without%20quotation%20or%20attribution.%20In%20the%20post%20on%20X%2C%20Oxman%20wrote%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20deeply%20apologize%20to%20Mattheck%20for%20inadvertently%20not%20citing%20him%20when%20I%20paraphrased.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22comp%20Matthech%20and%20Oxman%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F659722c76979d737182091a6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222295%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EGay%20faces%20some%20of%20the%20same%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20complaint%20sent%20to%20Havard%20claimed%20that%20her%201993%20article%20%26quot%3BBetween%20Black%20and%20White%3A%20The%20Complexity%20of%20Brazilian%20Race%20Relations%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20journal%20Origins%20contained%20numerous%20passages%20of%20text%20that%20closely%20mirrored%20writing%20by%20scholar%20David%20Covin%20without%20any%20mention%20of%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20Gay%20wrote%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3E%26quot%3BThe%20fundamental%20organizational%20unit%2C%20as%20approved%20by%20the%20founding%20National%20Assembly%20in%201978%2C%20was%20to%20be%20the%20Center%20of%20Struggle%20(Centro%20de%20Luta).%20Centers%20were%20to%20be%20formed%20in%20work%20areas%2C%20villages%2C%20prisons%2C%20candomble%20and%20umbanda%20temples%2C%20samba%20schools%2C%20churches%2C%20and%20favelas.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%201990%20article%20titled%20%26quot%3BAfrocentricity%20in%20O%20Movimento%20Negro%20Unificado%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20Journal%20of%20Black%2C%20Covin%2C%20by%20comparison%2C%20wrote%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20basic%20organizational%20structure%20which%20they%20approved%2C%20the%20Centers%20of%20Struggle%20were%20the%20fundamental%20organizational%20units.%20These%20were%20to%20be%20formed%20in%20work%20areas%2C%20villages%2C%20prisons%2C%20candombl%C3%A9%20and%20umbanda%20temples%2C%20samba%20schools%2C%20afox%C3%A9s%2C%20churches%2C%20and%20favelas.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EGay's%20plagiarism%20problems%20go%20beyond%20her%20dissertation%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGay's%20citation%20issues%20extend%20beyond%20her%20dissertation%20and%20to%20her%20academic%20writing.%20Eight%20of%20her%20published%20works%20have%20been%20flagged%20to%20Harvard%20for%20containing%20instances%20of%20plagiarism.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20has%20analyzed%20Oxman's%20dissertation%20for%20plagiarism%2C%20not%20her%20entire%20body%20of%20academic%20writings%2C%20and%20there%20has%20been%20much%20greater%20scrutiny%20of%20Gay's%20writing%20than%20Oxman's.%20So%20far%2C%20instances%20of%20plagiarism%20have%20only%20been%20reported%20as%20an%20issue%20in%20Oxman's%20dissertation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBailey%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20Oxman%20and%20Gay%20exemplified%20%26quot%3Bpoor%20writing%20habits%26quot%3B%20that%20he%20often%20sees%20in%20students%20who%20make%20citation%20a%20part%20of%20the%20editing%20process%20rather%20than%20the%20writing%20task.%20Cite%20as%20you%20write%20to%20avoid%20making%20these%20types%20of%20mistakes%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20indicates%20a%20bad%20process%20to%20drafting%20this%20stuff%2